iv><div id="entry_t1_vtl" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_vtl" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_vtl" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Warrigal/">Warrigal</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">26 June 2009 07:15:17AM</span><span class="votes " >3 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_vtl'] = ['2 points', '3 points', '4 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_vtl')">[+] (0 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_vtl" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_vtl" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Warrigal/">Warrigal</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">26 June 2009 07:15:17AM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_vtl'>3 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_vtl'] = ['2 points', '3 points', '4 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_vtl')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_vtl" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>On an advertisement for a fitness product: "WHAT'S STRONGER? YOU, or YOUR EXCUSES?"</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_vtl"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_vtl" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_vtl')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_vtl" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_vtl')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_vtl" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/10o/rationality_quotes_june_2009/vtl?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_vtl" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_vtl')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_vtl class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_vtl" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_vst" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_vst" class="parent"><a name="vst" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_vst" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_vst" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_vst" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Vladimir_Nesov/">Vladimir_Nesov</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">26 June 2009 02:18:04AM</span><span class="votes " >4 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_vst'] = ['3 points', '4 points', '5 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_vst')">[+] (0 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_vst" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_vst" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Vladimir_Nesov/">Vladimir_Nesov</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">26 June 2009 02:18:04AM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_vst'>4 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_vst'] = ['3 points', '4 points', '5 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_vst')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_vst" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><blockquote>
  <p>Loyalty mods don't whisper propaganda in your skull. They don't bombard you with images of the object of devotion while stimulating the pleasure centres of your brain, or cripple you with pain and nausea if you stray from correct thought. They don't cloud your mind with blissful euphoria, or feverish zealotry; nor do they trick you into accepting some flawed but elegant piece of casuistry. No brainwashing, no conditioning, no persuasion. A loyalty mod isn't an agent of change; it's the end product, a fait accompli. Not a cause for belief, but belief itself, belief made flesh - or rather, flesh made into belief.</p>
</blockquote>

<p>--Greg Egan, "Quarantine".</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_vst"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_vst" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_vst')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_vst" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_vst')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_vst" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/10o/rationality_quotes_june_2009/vst?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_vst" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_vst')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_vst class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_vst" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_vt1" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_vt1" class="parent"><a name="vt1" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_vt1" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_vt1" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_vt1" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/CronoDAS/">CronoDAS</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">26 June 2009 03:29:12AM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " >2 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_vt1'] = ['1 point', '2 points', '3 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_vt1')">[+] (0 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_vt1" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_vt1" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/CronoDAS/">CronoDAS</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">26 June 2009 03:29:12AM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_vt1'>2 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_vt1'] = ['1 point', '2 points', '3 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_vt1')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_vt1" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><blockquote>
  <p>So, if we can't derive 'ought' from 'is' - then we have no reason to keep 'ought' around at all. We have no reason not to discard it and toss it in the same bin with God, devils, souls, <a href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/rb/possibility_and_couldness/">[non-deterministic</a>] free will, and other mythical entities that more primitive cultures once accepted.</p>
</blockquote>

<p>-- Alonzo Fyfe</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_vt1"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_vt1" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_vt1')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_vt1" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_vt1')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_vt1" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/10o/rationality_quotes_june_2009/vt1?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_vt1" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_vt1')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_vt1 class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_vt1" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_voo" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_voo" class="parent"><a name="voo" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_voo" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_voo" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_voo" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Vladimir_Nesov/">Vladimir_Nesov</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">24 June 2009 05:19:24PM</span><span class="votes " >7 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_voo'] = ['6 points', '7 points', '8 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_voo')">[+] (0 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_voo" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_voo" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Vladimir_Nesov/">Vladimir_Nesov</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">24 June 2009 05:19:24PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_voo'>7 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_voo'] = ['6 points', '7 points', '8 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_voo')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_voo" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><blockquote>
  <p>"A few intellectually rigorous killjoys argued that any explanation to which humans could relate was probably anthropomorphic nonsense, but nobody invited them onto talk shows."</p>
</blockquote>

<p>--Greg Egan, "Quarantine".</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_voo"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_voo" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_voo')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_voo" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_voo')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_voo" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/10o/rationality_quotes_june_2009/voo?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_voo" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_voo')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_voo class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_voo" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_vom" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_vom" class="parent"><a name="vom" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_vom" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_vom" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_vom" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/CronoDAS/">CronoDAS</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">24 June 2009 04:43:39PM</span><span class="votes " >1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_vom'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_vom')">[+] (1 child)</a></div><div id="display_t1_vom" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_vom" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/CronoDAS/">CronoDAS</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">24 June 2009 04:43:39PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_vom'>1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_vom'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_vom')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_vom" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>"I hold that moral intuitions are nothing but learned prejudices. Historic examples from slavery to the divine right of kings to tortured confessions of witchcraft or Judaism to the subjugation of women to genocide all point to the fallibility of these 'moral intuitions'. There is absolutely no sense to the claim that its conclusions are to be adopted before those of a reasoned argument." - Alonzo Fyfe</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_vom"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_vom" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_vom')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_vom" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_vom')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_vom" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/10o/rationality_quotes_june_2009/vom?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_vom" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_vom')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_vom class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_vom" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_vom" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_vom" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_vp1" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_vp1" class="parent"><a name="vp1" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_vp1" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_vp1" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_vp1" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/conchis/">conchis</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">24 June 2009 08:03:57PM</span><span class="votes " >1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_vp1'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_vp1')">[+] (0 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_vp1" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_vp1" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/conchis/">conchis</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">24 June 2009 08:03:57PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_vp1'>1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_vp1'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_vp1')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_vp1" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>I'm not sure you can get anywhere without relying on intuitions at all. Some intuitions might hold more weight than others, but ultimately it's intuitions all the way down.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_vp1"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_vp1" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_vp1')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_vp1" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_vp1')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_vp1" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/10o/rationality_quotes_june_2009/vp1?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_vp1" href="#vom" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_vp1" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_vp1')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_vp1 class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_vp1" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_vli" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_vli" class="parent"><a name="vli" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_vli" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_vli" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_vli" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/CronoDAS/">CronoDAS</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date