15 June 2009 07:17:05PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_uzh'>4 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_uzh'] = ['3 points', '4 points', '5 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_uzh')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_uzh" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>Is it really true that playing the lottery makes you feel rich?  Can someone who has played the lottery corroborate on this?</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_uzh"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_uzh" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_uzh')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_uzh" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_uzh')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_uzh" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/10o/rationality_quotes_june_2009/uzh?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_uzh" href="#ux3" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_uzh" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_uzh')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_uzh class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_uzh" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_uzh" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_uzh" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_uzo" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_uzo" class="parent"><a name="uzo" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_uzo" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_uzo" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_uzo" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/MichaelBishop/">MichaelBishop</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">15 June 2009 07:28:38PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " >1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_uzo'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_uzo')">[+] (0 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_uzo" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_uzo" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/MichaelBishop/">MichaelBishop</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">15 June 2009 07:28:38PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_uzo'>1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_uzo'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_uzo')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_uzo" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>Or that voting makes you feel powerful?  I mean, maybe a little... not close to as much as performing well at work or in sport or in bed.  My initial comment was not intended to argue that his quote was dumb because I didn't think it was worth fighting that fight against the numerous people that apparently think it is a good quote.  But I can't pretend I like it.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_uzo"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_uzo" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_uzo')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_uzo" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_uzo')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_uzo" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/10o/rationality_quotes_june_2009/uzo?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_uzo" href="#uzh" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_uzo" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_uzo')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_uzo class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_uzo" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_uyj" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_uyj" class="parent"><a name="uyj" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_uyj" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_uyj" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " ><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_uyj" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/MichaelBishop/">MichaelBishop</a></span></strong></span>comment score below threshold<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_uyj')">[+] (30 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_uyj" class="" style='display:none'><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_uyj" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/MichaelBishop/">MichaelBishop</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">15 June 2009 04:27:23PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_uyj'>-4 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_uyj'] = ['-5 points', '-4 points', '-3 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_uyj')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_uyj" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>Ceteris Paribus, I prefer quotes from people who are well known, respected, and deserving of respect.</p>

