ormal/">orthonormal</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">15 June 2009 06:29:37PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_uz3'>5 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_uz3'] = ['4 points', '5 points', '6 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_uz3')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_uz3" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>Without context, I'm afraid I don't understand what this is supposed to signify regarding rationality.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_uz3"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_uz3" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_uz3')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_uz3" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_uz3')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_uz3" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/10o/rationality_quotes_june_2009/uz3?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_uz3" href="#uy7" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_uz3" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_uz3')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_uz3 class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_uz3" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_uz3" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_uz3" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_v56" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_v56" class="parent"><a name="v56" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_v56" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_v56" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_v56" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/RichardKennaway/">RichardKennaway</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">16 June 2009 07:55:06PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " >6 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_v56'] = ['5 points', '6 points', '7 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_v56')">[+] (3 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_v56" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_v56" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/RichardKennaway/">RichardKennaway</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">16 June 2009 07:55:06PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_v56'>6 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_v56'] = ['5 points', '6 points', '7 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_v56')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_v56" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>Yes, it's a bit of a koan, and somewhat tangential. It's about the ineluctability of reality, saying that while you <em>must</em> win, you may <em>not</em> win, even if you do everything right. Even the ultimate in rationality is not a get out of jail free card, neither in the backcountry nor anywhere else.</p>

